{{Infobox religious building | name = {{nihongo|'''Mitami Shrine'''|美多彌神社}} | image = Mitami-jinja2.jpg | caption = Mitami shrine | map_type = Japan | map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|34|28|30|N|135|29|08|E|region:JP_scale:30000_source:jawiki|display=title,inline}} | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | type = | deity = | founded_by = | established = | date_destroyed = | location = | website = | architecture_style = | festival = | leadership = }} '''Mitami Shrine''' ''Mitami-jinja'' 美多彌神社 (also 美多弥神社) is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[:en:Sakai|Sakai]], [[:en:Osaka Prefecture|Osaka Prefecture]], Japan. It is located in [[Senboku New Town]] near [[:en:Komyoike Station|Komyoike Station]]. It is accessible on the [[Nankai bus line]] or the [[:en:Semboku Rapid Railway|Semboku Rapid Railway]]. Mitami-jinja is mentioned in the [[:en:Heian period|Heian period]] chronicle ''[[Engishiki]]'' compiled in the early tenth century. The shrine buildings were destroyed by [[:en:Oda Nobunaga|Oda Nobunaga]]'s troops in 1577, but they were rebuilt in 1592 by Wada Dosan 和田道讃.
Deities enshrined here include [[Ame-no-Koyane]] no mikoto (天児屋根命), Kumano no ookami (熊野大神), Itsukushima no ookami (厳島大神), [[:en:Ookuninushi|Ookuninushi]] no mikoto (大国主命), [[Tenjin (kami)|Tenjin]] ([[Sugawara no Michizane]], 菅原大神), [[Hachiman]] (八幡大神), Kotohira ookami (琴平大神), [[Susanoo-no-Mikoto|Susanoo]] no mikoto (素盞鳴男命) and Mikumari no kami (天水分大神).
The shrine is famous locally for its comparatively large population of ''[[:en:Lithocarpus glaber|Lithocarpus glaber]]'' (''Shiribukagashi'' シリブカガシ). {{Commons Category|Mitami-jinja}}
